<%- include('partials/header') %>
<style>
  /* LTP price flash — green when ticking up, red when ticking down. */
  @keyframes ltp-up-flash   { 0% { background-color: rgba(16,185,129,.35);} 100% { background-color: transparent;} }
  @keyframes ltp-down-flash { 0% { background-color: rgba(244,63,94,.35); } 100% { background-color: transparent;} }
  .ltp-up   { animation: ltp-up-flash   .6s ease-out; color: #047857; }
  .ltp-down { animation: ltp-down-flash .6s ease-out; color: #be123c; }
  .how-it-works > summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .how-it-works > summary { list-style: none; }
  .how-it-works > summary::before { content: '▸ '; color: #6b7280; }
  .how-it-works[open] > summary::before { content: '▾ '; }
  .how-it-works[open] > summary .text-xs { display: none; }
  .how-it-works h3 { margin: 0; }
</style>
<div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-4">
  <h1 class="mb-0">Premium Trigger</h1>
  <div class="flex gap-2">
    <a href="/premium-trigger/settings" class="btn">Settings</a>
    <a href="/premium-trigger/backtest" class="btn">Backtest</a>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="card mb-4">
  <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3">
    <span id="modeBadge" class="mode-badge mode-paper">PAPER</span>
    <button id="toggleBtn" class="btn-primary">…</button>
    <button id="exitBtn" class="btn-warn">Square off all</button>
    <button id="restrikeCe" class="btn-secondary">Restrike CE</button>
    <button id="restrikePe" class="btn-secondary">Restrike PE</button>
    <label class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm cursor-pointer select-none ml-2 px-2 py-1 rounded border border-line">
      <input type="checkbox" id="autoRestrikeToggle" /> Auto-restrike on drift
    </label>
    <span id="status" class="muted text-sm ml-auto"></span>
  </div>
  <div id="meta" class="muted text-sm mt-3 flex flex-wrap gap-x-4 gap-y-1"></div>
  <div id="wsDiag" class="text-xs mt-2 px-3 py-2 rounded border border-line bg-surface-muted hidden"></div>
  <p class="error mt-2" id="err"></p>
</div>

<details class="card mb-4 how-it-works">
  <summary class="cursor-pointer select-none flex items-center justify-between gap-3">
    <span class="font-semibold text-ink-900">How it works</span>
    <span class="text-xs muted">Click to expand</span>
  </summary>
  <div class="mt-4 grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-2 text-sm leading-relaxed">
    <div>
      <h3>What this strategy does</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-ink-700">
        <strong>Sells</strong> (shorts) the CE and PE legs when their
        premium <strong>rises through your trigger</strong>, then
        <strong>buys back</strong> when premium falls to <span class="pnl-pos">target</span>
        (profit) or rises to <span class="pnl-neg">stoploss</span>
        (loss). Each leg runs independently.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3>Tick state machine</h3>
      <ol class="mt-2 space-y-1 text-ink-700 list-decimal list-inside">
        <li><strong>Re-arm</strong> — LTP back inside rearm window → <span class="pill pill-mute">armed</span></li>
        <li><strong>Drift watch</strong> — LTP outside window starts auto-restrike timer</li>
        <li><strong>Day-loss check</strong> — block new entries if cap hit</li>
        <li><strong>Capture &amp; confirm</strong> — two ticks: snap trigger, then confirm</li>
        <li><strong>Exit</strong> — buy back on target or stoploss</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3>Entry sequence</h3>
      <ol class="mt-2 space-y-1 text-ink-700 list-decimal list-inside">
        <li>Premium enters the rearm window around <em>entryTrigger</em> → leg <strong>arms</strong>.</li>
        <li>Next qualifying tick is <strong>captured</strong> as the trigger price.</li>
        <li>Following tick at <em>triggerPrice + reentryOffset</em> <strong>confirms</strong> → place <strong>SELL MKT</strong> (MIS).</li>
        <li>If LTP fades by <em>captureFadeThreshold</em> while waiting, the trigger is dropped.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3>Target &amp; Stoploss</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-ink-700">
        Computed from the actual fill price, per‑leg, in rupees:
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-1 text-ink-700 space-y-0.5">
        <li><span class="pnl-pos">Target price</span> = entryPrice − target (first entry uses <em>target</em>, re-entries use <em>reentryTarget</em>)</li>
        <li><span class="pnl-neg">SL price</span> = entryPrice + stoploss</li>
        <li>Whichever is hit first → <strong>BUY MKT</strong> to close. Net P&amp;L = points × qty × lotSize − charges.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mt-2 muted text-xs">
        Worked example: trigger 250, target 5, SL 10 — SELL fills at 253, target at 248, SL at 263.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3>Auto-restrike on drift</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-ink-700">
        If a leg sits outside its rearm window for <em>restrikeDwellSec</em>
        (and <em>restrikeCooldownSec</em> has passed since the last
        rotation), the engine re-scans the chain and rotates to a new
        OTM strike whose premium is back in‑window. Never rotates while
        a leg is SHORT. After 3 cycles where no in-window strike exists
        (chain decayed), entry can fire on the available premium
        (<em>loosened mode</em>).
      </p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3>Manual controls</h3>
      <ul class="mt-2 text-ink-700 space-y-0.5">
        <li><strong>Start / Stop</strong> — toggles the engine. Stop does not square off.</li>
        <li><strong>Square off all</strong> — BUY MKT close on every open leg.</li>
        <li><strong>Restrike CE / PE</strong> — force-close (if SHORT) and rotate to a fresh OTM strike. Operator override; ignores dwell &amp; cooldown.</li>
        <li><strong>Auto-restrike on drift</strong> — enables the watcher above.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3>EOD &amp; safety</h3>
      <ul class="mt-2 text-ink-700 space-y-0.5">
        <li><strong>EOD auto-exit</strong> at <em>eodAutoExit</em> (default 15:20 IST) — squares off + stops.</li>
        <li><strong>Daily loss cap</strong> (<em>maxDailyLoss</em>) — once realised loss ≤ −cap, no new entries on either leg until the config is re-saved.</li>
        <li><strong>SL lock</strong> — a leg that hit SL won't re-enter the same session.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3>Paper vs Live</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-ink-700">
        Paper mode uses the same tick stream and quote endpoints; only
        order placement is simulated (orders get a <code>PAPER-…</code> ID
        and never reach the broker). Live mode places <code>MIS / MKT</code>
        orders via Kotak Neo. The mode badge at the top reflects which
        you're running.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="lg:col-span-2 border-t border-line pt-4">
      <h3>Broker bracket exits (opt-in)</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-ink-700">
        When <em>Use broker bracket exits</em> is enabled in settings,
        the engine switches to the standard option-selling pattern:
      </p>
      <ol class="mt-2 space-y-1 text-ink-700 list-decimal list-inside">
        <li>SELL entry fills (MIS · MKT) — same as today.</li>
        <li>Place <strong>SL-M BUY</strong> at <em>entry + stoploss</em> as the trigger.</li>
        <li>Place <strong>LIMIT BUY</strong> at <em>entry − target</em>.</li>
        <li>Status is polled every <em>bracketStatusPollMs</em>. When one fills, the other is cancelled (OCO).</li>
        <li>Restrike, manual exit, and EOD all <strong>cancel both children first</strong> before flattening with MKT.</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="mt-2 text-ink-700">
        A tick-based <strong>safety hammer</strong> stays armed: if LTP
        overshoots SL by <em>bracketSafetyOvershoot</em> and the broker
        hasn't reported a fill within <em>bracketSafetyTimeoutMs</em>, the
        engine cancels both children and flattens with MKT. Paper mode
        simulates the brackets so paper P&amp;L matches live behavior.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</details>

